The paper discusses a method for improving the computational efficiency of nonlinear support vector machines, which is a common problem in machine learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most likely category. Additionally, the use of PETSc for implementation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also discusses the use of SVMs in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which are both relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the issue of imbalanced class sizes, which is a common problem in data science and may suggest that the paper is also relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
